      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This example has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rod bearing replacement to ensure long-term mechanical reliability. The rear subframe has been reinforced to address common chassis fatigue, maintaining structural rigidity during spirited cornering. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. The suspension retains its communicative geometry, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration for precise turn-in. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain remains exceptionally tight with a linear power delivery and crisp throttle response. A mechanically sound specimen for the purist who prioritizes performance and engineering integrity.",
